148 5. WILLIAM GEE. To be buried in the Conventual Church of the Friars Minors, “ coram ymagine 'beate Marie Virginis in nave eiusdem ecclesie.''

Will dated 27 September, 148 5. Proved 3 November, 1485. 17 Logge.

Gee was buried in the second row in the third bay of the North Aisle, his grave being the last but one from the arcade. The

Image of the Virgin must be the same as that referred to in the Will of William Hoton in 1447. Grey Friars, p. 120.
